<div><h3>BIOT 2100 - Good Clinical Practice: Exploring the Basics </h3>  <p><hr>The course will provide an overview of the stages and fundamentals of Good Clinical Practice (GCP), which is recognized globally as a standard and ethical way of testing human subjects.  During the course, students will learn relevant US FDA regulations for GCP which meets the guideline from the Society of Quality Assurance (SQA).  Other guidelines from agencies such as ICH or ISO will be discussed.  Students will be presented a comprehensive view of the GCP practices in human clinical trials and the auditing process of parties and sites involved in the clinical study.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=99948" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99948&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99948&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt8829" target="_blank"> BIOT 1000 - Introduction to Biotechnology</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> </p>

